Vraisemblance et biais de lâ€™algorithme

analyse <- function(nt,nj) {
  
  print(paste0("Analyse de scÃ©nario avec ",nt," cartes communes connues et ",nj," adversaire",
               ifelse(nj>1,"s","")))
  
  bd = read.csv(paste0("sim_nouvel_algo_T",nt,"_",nj,"j.csv"), sep="\t")
  data = data.frame(algo=bd$Pr_algo, y=bd$Pr_algo-bd$Pr_sim, pr=bd$ValP)
  
  # Q-Q plot
  par(mfrow=c(1,2))
  n = dim(data)[1]
  plot(seq(1/n,1,1/n), data$pr, ylab="Valeur-P", xlab="Quantile", main="Quantile-quantile")
  abline(0,1,col="red")
  plot(seq(1/n,.1,1/n), data$pr[1:(n/10)], ylab="Valeur-P", ylim=c(0,0.1), xlim=c(0,.1),
       main=paste0("QQ, ",n/10," pires valeurs"), xlab="Quantile")
  abline(0,1,col="red")
  
  # Proportion de biais positif
  sous_bd = data[which(data$y<data$algo),] # Les sims Ã  0% auront toujours un biais positif...
  mu = mean(sous_bd$y>0)
  print("Proportion biais positif")
  print(paste0(mu," -> Valeur-P: ", 1-pnorm(abs(mu-0.5)/sqrt(.25/dim(sous_bd)[1]))))
  
  # RÃ©gression pour estimer le biais en fonction de la probabilitÃ© Ã©valuÃ©e par l'algorithme
  reg_base = glm(y ~ poly(algo,3), data=data)
  data = data[order(data$algo),]
  x = data$algo
  y = predict(reg_base, newdata=data)
  reg_aj = glm((y/sqrt(algo*(1-algo))) ~ poly(algo,3), data=data)
  y2 = predict(reg_aj, newdata=data)
  
  plot(x, y, type="l", ylim=c(min(c(0,y,y2)),max(c(y,y2))), main="Biais estimÃ©",
       xlab="ProbabilitÃ© de l'algo", ylab="Biais")
  lines(x, y2, lty=2)
  abline(0,0,lty=3)
  abline(v=.5,lty=3)
  hist(data$y, breaks=100, xlab="biais", main="FrÃ©quence des biais", freq=F)
  biais_sig = (sum(summary(reg_base)$coefficients[,4]<0.05)>0)|(sum(summary(reg_aj)$coefficients[,4]<0.05)>0)
  
  print("RÃ©gression de base")
  print(summary(reg_base)$coefficients)
  print("RÃ©gression ajustÃ©e")
  print(summary(reg_aj)$coefficients)
  print(paste0("Au moins un coefficient de rÃ©gression statistiquement significatif: ",biais_sig))
}
